{"word":"ἀντιτάσσω","slug":"ἀντιτάσσω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀντιτάσσω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to set opposite to, range in battle against</i>, <el>τινά τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>τι πρός τι</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschines'>Aeschin.</a></b>:—so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> also <i>to set oneself against, meet face to face, meet in battle</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be drawn out against</i>, <el>τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; <el>πρός τινα</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; <el>κατά τινα</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}